    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I have investigated this, and it seems we purposefully don't allow leading zero byte arrays:\r\n\r\n```\r\n              /* bytearray to number, verify no leading zbytes */ \r\n              [with,\r\n                _sub,\r\n                352 <inp>,\r\n                [with,\r\n                  _el1,\r\n                  [mload, [add, 32, _sub]],\r\n                  [with,\r\n                    _len,\r\n                    [clamp, 0, [mload, _sub], 32],\r\n                    [seq,\r\n                      [assert, [or, [iszero, _len], [div, _el1, [exp, 256, 31]]]],\r\n                      [clamp, [mload, 96], [div, _el1, [exp, 256, [sub, 32, _len]]], [mload, 64]]]]]]],\r\n```\r\nBy passing in a zero byte string the transaction fails.",
